#-Function--cleanup
  Function: cleanup
      Desc: a call to this function is made in the trap EXIT command.
          : on exiting the script this function will always be called.
          : you should define your own cleanup function to delete temporary
          : files and other detritus before terminating.
          : if you are not using the exit_if_already_running function
          : (in other words, you are allowing multiple instances of this
          : script to run at the same time) then you can delete the deletion
          : of the .lock file.
  Synopsis: cleanup [exitcode]
  See_Also: trap.set trap.function, exit_if_already_running
   Example: cleanup
#-Function--cleanup-----------------------------------------------------------
